### Hadith 1:465

*Narrated 'Aisha:*

(the wife of the Prophet) I had seen my parents following Islam since I
attained the age of puberty. Not a day passed but the Prophet visited
us, both in the mornings and evenings. My father Abii Bakr thought of
building a mosque in the courtyard of his house and he did so. He used
to pray and recite the Qur'an in it. The pagan women and their children
used to stand by him and look at him with surprise. Abu Bakr was a
Softhearted person and could not help weeping while reciting the Quran.
The chiefs of the Quraish pagans became afraid of that (i.e. that their
children and women might be affected by the recitation of Quran)."

